title.rendered: Quetta vs Multan, Pakistan T20 League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

There is no update on Sarfaraz Ahmed, who missed the last clash due to injury.

Quetta: Martin Guptill, Jason Roy, Will Smeed, Mohammad Hafeez, Iftikhar Ahmed, Umar Akmal (wk), Mohammad Nawaz (c), Dwaine Pretorius, Mohammad Hasnain, Naseem Shah, Aimal Khan

Multan: Shan Masood, Mohammad Rizwan (c & wk), Rilee Rossouw, Tim David, Khushdil Shah, Kieron Pollard, Anwar Ali, Usama Mir, Abbas Afridi, Sheldon Cottrell, Ihsanullah

Pitch Report

Venue: Pindi Club Ground, Rawalpindi

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 236

2nd innings average score: 209

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Multan would be expecting another solid foundation from openers Shan Masood and Mohammad Rizwan who are their top run-getters against Quetta: 566 runs at a combined average of 47.

Ihsanullah and Abbas Afridi are the top wicket-takers in the tournament. Together, they have registered two four-fers and a five-fer to aggregate 35 wickets. Ihsanullah picked up five wickets when the sides clashed earlier.

The clash hints at another Rilee Rossouw show. He has hit a century and two half-centuries in six matches against Quetta. He averages 68 at the venue, including a score of 121 in the last match.

Jason Roy has registered a century and a fifty in three innings, while his opening partner Martin Guptill averages 107 at the venue.

Mohammad Nawaz (71 runs and five wickets) and Mohammad Hasnain (eight wickets) have featured in the Best11 in three of the last five matches.

Four centuries and four half-centuries have been scored in the last three matches at the venue.
